/*
  ================================================================
  ROCKET TELEMETRY — Full 6-DOF Kalman Filter
  Teensy 4.1 | USB Serial Monitor | long double precision
  ================================================================

  Sistem:
    - Rocket simulation reaching ~4000m altitude
    - Two pressure sensors → Sensor Fusion (merged via Kalman)
    - Full 6-DOF state vector:
        x = [irtifa, hız_z, ivme_z, roll, pitch, yaw]
    - Processing time reported in µs per step

  Usage (Serial Monitor, 115200 baud):
    > start        → start simulation
    > step         → advance one step
    > run N        → run N steps automatically
    > reset        → reset
    > status       → show current state
    > help         → command list

  Matrix dimensions:
    State (x):          6×1
    Transition (F):          6×6
    Noise (Q):        6×6
    Measurement (H):          4×6  (2 pressure + 2 accelerometer)
    Measurement noise (R): 4×4
    Covariance (P):      6×6
    Kalman gain (K): 6×4

  ================================================================
*/

